acceptanceRequired.description: Specifies if the match that was created with this configuration must be accepted by matched players.

acceptanceTimeoutSeconds.description: The length of time (in seconds) to wait for players to accept a proposed match, if acceptance is required.

additionalPlayerCount.description: The number of player slots in a match to keep open for future players.

backfillMode.description: The method used to backfill game sessions that are created with this matchmaking configuration.

creationTime.description: The time when the Matchmaking Configuration was created.

customEventData.description: Information to be added to all events related to this matchmaking configuration.

description.description: A human-readable description of the matchmaking configuration.

flexMatchMode.description: Indicates whether this matchmaking configuration is being used with GameLift hosting or as a standalone matchmaking solution.

gameProperties.description: One or more custom game properties. See below.

gameSessionData.description: A set of custom game session properties.

gameSessionQueueArns.description: The ARNs of the GameLift game session queue resources.

notificationTarget.description: An SNS topic ARN that is set up to receive matchmaking notifications.

requestTimeoutSeconds.description: The maximum duration, in seconds, that a matchmaking ticket can remain in process before timing out.

ruleSetName.description: A rule set names for the matchmaking rule set to use with this configuration.

tags.description: Key-value map of resource tags. .If configured with a provider `default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

tagsAll.description: A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.
